docs.lead_paragraph: These volumes contain the first satisfactory story of the life of a woman concerning whom decidedly erroneous notions have been entertained. From them it is possible to learn just what sort of woman Miss Edgeworth was, and to understand how she came to occupy her unique position in litrature.

headline.main: MARIA EDGE WORTH AS SHE WAS; THE LIFE AND LETTERS OF MARIA EDGEWORTH. Edited by Augustus J.C. Hare. Two volumes, 16mc. Boston: Roughton, Mifflin & Co. $2 per volume.
